    <h1>RETINOL</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201023/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-23"><time>2020-10-23</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>This is an in­gre­di­ent that has been around for some time, but started sur­fac­ing in main­stream con­scious­ness only in re­cent years.</p>
    <p>A de­riv­a­tive of vitamin A, over-the-counter retinol is an anti-age­ing favourite among der­ma­tol­o­gists and skin­care junkies.</p>
    <p>Mul­ti­ple stud­ies have shown its cos­metic ben­e­fits that range from smooth­ing skin and in­creas­ing cell turnover, to stim­u­lat­ing col­la­gen pro­duc­tion and im­prov­ing pig­men­ta­tion.</p>
    <p>Sounds like a mir­a­cle prod­uct? It comes with a price – retinol can have side ef­fects in­clud­ing dry­ness, peel­ing and ir­ri­ta­tion, es­pe­cially at the be­gin­ning.</p>
    <p>Be­cause of its po­tency, ex­perts ad­vise in­tro­duc­ing retinol into your night-time rou­tine slowly. Start with once or twice a week and grad­u­ally build up fre­quency once your skin can han­dle it.</p>
    <p>Re­mem­ber to slather on sun­screen the next day, as your skin may be ex­tra sen­si­tised in the sun­light.</p>
    <p>TRY:</p>
    <p>1. Glow Recipe Avo­cado Melt Retinol Eye Sleep­ing Mask, $64</p>
    <p>2. Olay Re­gener­ist Retinol24 Night Serum, $54.90</p>

